name: Is That All There Is
comments: Dan Daniels was a NYC disc jockey when he was contacted by Epic records about narrating over a music track the label had already produced — "Is That All There Is." Leiber & Stoller protested (which was their right since the song hadn't been released by anyone yet) and Epic pulled Daniels' record from commercial distribution. Apparently, it did make it to at least one radio station in Longview, Texas, KFRO-AM, before the release was terminated.

name: Eres tú
comments: Peaked at #8 in the Flanders region of Belgium. Also peaked at #25 in the Wallonia region. Spain's entry in the 1973 Eurovision Song Contest, where it reached second place. The single release became a world-wide hit: #3 in The Netherlands and New Zealand, #8 in Belgium and #9 on the US Billboard Hot 100.
